% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% mcovar_mask - Compute Mean and Std. Dev. Vectors and Covariance Matrix
%
%  DESCRIPTION
% This program computes the mean and standard deviation vectors and covariance matrix of the set of data vectors supplied in the input data object specified with [-i]. All WxHxDxT data is used, creating the optional outputs:
% A mean vector of E elements (if the parameter [-omean] is used)
% A standard deviation vector of E elements (if the parameter [-ostddev] is used)
% A covariance matrix of ExE elements (if the parameter [-ocovar] is used). 
% The difference from this operator and the similar operator mcovar in the MATRIX toolbox is that this one consider the mask on the input object, ignoring points which are masked. Also, the normalization can be done either to N points or N-1 points, where N=WxHxDxT.
% The output will always of of type DOUBLE. Complex data cannot be used.
%
%  
%
%  EXAMPLES
% All examples for the Classify toolbox are listed on the Classify Toolbox Manual. There isn't any example for this program - usually its associated lkroutine is called from the cmaxlik_signature and cmindist_signature operators to get the mean vector, covariance matrix and standard deviations for the signatures.
